Prince Charles announced his engagement to Camilla Parker Bowles, with a civil ceremony planned at Windsor Castle.
Despite some opposition, Archbishop of Canterbury Rowan Williams welcomed the news.
Prince William and Prince Harry expressed their happiness for their father.
Camilla will not be Queen but will hold the title of HRH Duchess of Cornwall.
The couple's relationship has endured despite challenges, and they genuinely care for each other.
Camilla's support for Charles has been unwavering.
The marriage will not replicate Charles and Diana's, but it signifies a new chapter for the royal family.
